The paper deals with the maximum bipartite matching problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The stochastic settings considered in the paper involve probabilities and randomness, which are typical topics in game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of linear programming (LP) to upper bound the optimum also suggests that the paper may belong to the information theory (cs.IT) category. Finally, the proposed algorithm involves optimization and decision-making, which are common themes in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
